Play-set button

This button has similar functionality as the A->B
button on the xmcd main window.  It is used to define
the start and end points of a segment.  The button label
is presented differently than on the main window button
to emphasize its function, and there are arrows that
point to the start and end position text boxes during
the definition process.

During normal audio playback, click this button
once to define the start of the segment (at this time
the program mode indicator will flash "a->?").  Click
it a second time to define the end of the segment
(the indicator goes blank).  Audio playback will
continue normally, and you may use the "Add" button to
add the defined segment to the list.  Note that this is
somewhat different than the behavior of the A->B button
on the main window.

You can define the Segment Play mode start and end
points only if audio playback is in progress, and is
not in paused state.  Also, you cannot enter Segment
Play mode during shuffle playback or if a program
sequence is defined.

During the "a->?" phase, you may use the previous/next
track, previous/next index, REW/FF, or the keypad to
locate the end point quickly.  If you click the Stop
button, a->? phase will be canceled and xmcd will go
to normal playback mode.

